# Pre-Commit Standards (Husky / lint-staged)

Every code change must pass lint **before** the user commits. Treat lint failures as blocking bugs — fix them in the same task, not after a failed commit.

## Before Finishing Any Task

1. Run lint on **every file you created or modified**:
   `npm run lint` or `npx oxlint <changed-files>`
2. Run `npm run build` after substantive UI/API work.
3. Do not commit `.env`, secrets, or credential files.

## Lint (oxlint)

- Fix errors in files you touched; do not leave parse errors or obvious unused imports in new code.
- Match existing JSX/JS style in the file (imports, Tailwind tokens, component patterns).

## Commit Messages (`.husky/commit-msg` + **commit-rabbit** skill)

Format: `<type>(<scope>): <description>` (description 1–100 chars)

```
feat(vle): add wallet navbar layout matching app shell
fix(auth): refresh VLE token before dashboard API calls
chore(deps): upgrade vite to 8.1.1
```

Valid types: `feat`, `fix`, `chore`, `docs`, `style`, `refactor`, `test`, `perf`, `ci`, `build`, `revert`

**Website scopes:** `vle`, `auth`, `wallet`, `app`, `login`, `reports`, `sos`, `mental`, `booktest`, `coordinator`, `vite`, `proxy`, `ui`, `deps`

Use the **commit-rabbit** skill (`.cursor/skills/commit-rabbit/`) when drafting commit messages.

## Do Not

- Commit without lint-checking your own edits
- Suggest commit messages that violate Conventional Commits
- Expand scope beyond what the user asked (see `setu-website-standards.mdc`)
